Pensioners in Northdale had their electrical fixtures explode during a power surge. (Kerushun Pillay) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories FIVE households on Dresda Road in Northdale had all their 
appliances blown out by an apparent electrical surge last Tuesday. Now the residents — all of whom are pensioners — say they will have 
to wait as long as six months for the Msunduzi Municipality to say whether the 
City will foot the bill for the damage. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  